tyle=3D"margin:10px 0">A few months ago, when I said xAI and Grok could cat=
ch up to or even beat OpenAI and Anthropic by the end of the year, a lot of=
 people in here called it blind Elon fanboy talk.</p><p style=3D"margin:10p=
x 0">Turns out there=E2=80=99s real movement happening.</p><p style=3D"marg=
in:10px 0">The big development is the xAI Cursor partnership!  AI Coding ha=
s the best product market fit of all AI tools and Anthropic leads, OpenAI s=
econd.... but for a while there Cursor was top dog but ran out of compute. =
 Cursor is an AI coding tool that exploded from $100M to $2B in yearly reve=
nue in just over a year. It became the favorite of serious developers becau=
se it doesn=E2=80=99t just chat with you. It has a smart =E2=80=9Cworkflow =
layer=E2=80=9D (called the agent harness) that understands your entire proj=
ect, edits multiple files, and actually helps you get real coding work done=
=2E</p><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">Cursor=
 just released a NEW coding model tha=
t performs at the level of the two top models but costs much less. Rem cost=
 is everything.  Teaming up with xAI/SpaceX gives Cursor access to xAI=E2=
=80=99s massive supercomputer cluster (the biggest in the world) and lets x=
AI use Cursor=E2=80=99s powerful workflow system.</p><p style=3D"margin:10p=
x 0">Raw AI models are becoming more similar. The real advantage now comes =
from who has the best system on top of the model + huge computing power. xA=
I just got both.  ALso note xAI never had an enterprise game... now they do=
=2E Final note on this... xAI have opti=
on to buy cursor for $60BN. </p><h2>Si=
mple Sum-of-the-Parts View</h2><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">If xAI + Cursor c=
an reach performance levels comparable to Anthropic, the combined business =
could reasonably be valued in the $1.2 trillion range. That single move wou=
ld also place SpaceX at roughly $800 billion on a sum-of-the-parts basis (w=
hich is stooopid cheap).</p><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">Elon does not just h=
ave the most compute and control it all, he also just inserted the missing =
piece (the harness + enterprise distribution) at a time when pure model sca=
ling is losing its edge. That=E2=80=99s how you change the valuation math q=
uickly. xAI went from =E2=80=9Cbehind=E2=80=9D to holding a credible path i=
n enterprise agentic coding with one of the largest compute clusters on the=
 planet. That=E2=80=99s the real story.</p><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">As I =
have also said for a year now</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">At =
the end of the day he with the most coherent compute wins...</p></blockquot=
e><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">This doesn=E2=80=99t mean xAI has already won.=
 But it gives them a credible, fast path to close the gap in the areas that=
 matter most right now =E2=80=94 especially building useful AI that can act=
ually code and work autonomously.</p><p style=3D"margin:10px 0">The =E2=80=
=9CElon fanboy=E2=80=9D crowd might want to slow down on the mocking. The c=
